<!DOCTYPE html>
<h1 id="name">Shane Evans</h1>
<h3 id="title">VP, Business Solutions&ndash;Retail</h3>
<div id="bio">
	<h3>VP, Business Solutions&ndash;Retail</h3>
	<div id="preview">
		<p>Shane Evans has more than 15 years of executive-level experience.</p>
		<p>He drives growth and creates value as head of Retail and International business at Mindshare.</p>
	</div>
	<p>Shane&rsquo;s passion for technology and developing new ways to leverage SaaS applications to aggregate, analyze, and disseminate information has helped companies drive additional sales and significant growth. He has worked closely with many global brands including Walgreens, Foot Locker, American Express, Aaron&rsquo;s, and Service Master.</p>
	<p>Shane leads a team of retail professionals committed to enhancing overall experience for the brands they work with. In addition, he coordinates Mindshare&rsquo;s international efforts.</p>
	<p>Before joining Mindshare, Shane was president of Conexus Network, a triple-play media provider that delivers voice, video, and data throughout master-planned communities.</p>
	<p>Since joining Mindshare, Shane has been committed to becoming a customer experience expert. He feels that by knowing the industry inside and out, he can truly help clients create world-class customer experience programs. He is constantly reading and studying any information available related to customer experience.</p>
	<p>Shane is continually moving and improving. It&rsquo;s one of his defining characteristics. In 2012, he competed in his first full-distance Ironman triathlon in St. George, Utah. The event is one of his most treasured experiences. Due to high winds in both the swim and bike portions of the race, only 29% of entrants finished&mdash;making this particular Ironman event the most difficult to date. Shane finished the race, earning his place as an elite competitor.</p>
	<p>Shane received a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business information systems from the University of Utah.</p>
</div>